00:24:12.360 --> 00:24:13.980
given what Google.org
org does, but I

00:24:13.980 --> 00:24:15.960
think that the first
thing people leap to is,

00:24:15.960 --> 00:24:18.480
like, let's figure out
how to use technology.

00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:20.640
And I think that
using technology

00:24:20.640 --> 00:24:23.370
is absolutely a powerful
tool that the social sector

00:24:23.370 --> 00:24:25.830
generally does not know
how to use well enough.

00:24:25.830 --> 00:24:28.290
But I think, equally,
if not more so,

00:24:28.290 --> 00:24:30.360
it's how we build
the technology.

00:24:30.360 --> 00:24:33.180
I mean, Google is
not outstanding

00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:34.964
only because of the
technology it builds,

00:24:34.964 --> 00:24:35.880
but it's the process--

00:24:35.880 --> 00:24:36.480
JACQUELLINE FULLER: The system.

00:24:36.480 --> 00:24:38.355
ANN MEI CHANG: --by
which we build it, right?

00:24:38.355 --> 00:24:41.130
I often give the example of,
everyone thinks of Google

00:24:41.130 --> 00:24:44.050
as one of the most innovative
companies on the planet.

00:24:44.050 --> 00:24:47.250
